data.chText: 优先事项；最重要的事；首要事情
data.enText: something that you think is more important than other things and should be dealt with first

data.chText: 我们的头等大事是提高水平。
data.enText: Our first priority is to improve standards.

data.chText: 在他的心目中，金融安全是十分重要的一环。
data.enText: Financial security was high on his list of priorities .

data.chText: 你需要把自己的事情分出轻重缓急。
data.enText: You need to get your priorities right (= decide what is important to you) .

data.chText: 你需要把个人事情的轻重缓急分清楚。
data.enText: You need to get your priorities straight .
the most important place among various things that have to be done or among a group of people

data.chText: 俱乐部成员享有优先权。
data.enText: Club members will be given priority .

data.chText: 研制新的疫苗将排在其他一切医学研究之前。
data.enText: The search for a new vaccine will take priority over all other medical research.

data.chText: 优先事项，比如无住房家庭的问题，得到优先处理。
data.enText: Priority cases, such as homeless families, get dealt with first.
the right of a vehicle to go before other traffic at a particular place on a road

data.chText: 在这个路口，公共汽车有优先通行权。
data.enText: Buses have priority at this junction.

simple_means.memory_skill: prior 优先（的）+ ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 先；优先权

tr: status established in order of importance or urgency
example: ...its precedence as the world's leading manufacturer of pharmaceuticals
national independence takes priority over class struggle

value.def: If something is a priority, it is the most important thing you have to do or deal with, or must be done or dealt with before everything else you have to do.

example.ex: Being a parent is her first priority...
example.tran: 做好母亲是她的头等大事。

example.ex: The government's priority is to build more power plants...
example.tran: 政府的首要任务是建造更多的发电站。

example.ex: Getting your priorities in order is a good way to not waste energy on meaningless pursuits.
example.tran: 将事情按优先顺序排列能有效地避免把精力浪费在无意义的工作上。

value.tran: 优先事项；最重要的事；当务之急

value.def: If you give priority to something or someone, you treat them as more important than anything or anyone else.

example.ex: The school will give priority to science, maths and modern languages...
example.tran: 学校将重点发展理科、数学和现代语言。

example.ex: The proposals deserve support as they give priority to the needs of children.
example.tran: 这些提议值得拥护，因为它们优先考虑了儿童的需求。

value.def: If something takes priority or has priority over other things, it is regarded as being more important than them and is dealt with first.

example.ex: The fight against inflation took priority over measures to combat the deepening recession...
example.tran: 抵制通货膨胀比抑制日益加剧的经济衰退更为重要。

example.ex: I disagree with the premise that economic development has priority over the environment.
example.tran: 我不赞成经济发展应优先于环境保护这个前提。

partsOfSpeech.dec: prim 第一，引申为“主要的” + e → 最初的；基本的
prim 第一，引申为“主要的” + acy 表性质 → 主要地位；重要性
prim 第一，引申为“主要的” + ary …的 → 最初的；根本的
prim 第一，引申为“主要的” + er 表物 → 第一本书 → 初级读本
prim 第一，引申为“主要的” + ev 时代 + al …的 → 最早的时代 → 远古的
prim 第一，引申为“主要的” + itive …的 → 原始的
primo〔= prim〕第一，引申为“主要的” + genit 产生 + or 表人 → 最早产生的人 → 始祖
prin 第一，引申为“主要的” + ce → 王位的第一继承人 → 王子
prin 第一，引申为“主要的” + cip 抓 + al 表人 → 作为第一〔要务〕来抓 → 最重要的
prin 第一，引申为“主要的” + cip 抓 + le 做某种动作时所使用的东西 → 握住主要〔原则〕→ 原则
pri 第一，引申为“主要的” + or 表状态 → 排在第一的 → 优先的
prior 优先（的）+ ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 先；优先权
